snippet.title: Alpine PND-K3 - GPS receiver
snippet.description: With the new interface and additional navigation features, the Alpine PND-K3 is an improvement over the company's previous in-car GPS, but the expensive price tag is a turn-off, especially when you can get more for less.

snippet.title: Samsung YP-K3
snippet.description: The Samsung YP-K3 may not be a Nano-killer, but it's definitely a solid choice for those who want a simple, sexy player that's not too hard on the wallet.

snippet.title: Kinesis K3 Wind and Solar Charger

snippet.title: Samsung YP-K3
snippet.description: The Samsung YP-K3 MP3 player may not be a Nano killer, but it's definitely a solid choice for those who want a simple, sexy player that's not too hard on the wallet.

snippet.title: Photos: Samsung K3
snippet.description: The K3 is quite possibly the best looking flash player out there, and the sound quality is worth hearing. The player's intuitiveness and responsive interface are sure to please, though you'd better be cool with touch-sensitive controls and no tactile feedback. For a player that's so light on features, the K3 is still pretty satisfying.

snippet.title: Alpine slashes price on its PND-K3 GPS
snippet.description: Alpine Electronics announces that it has reduced the price of its Alpine PND-K3 in-car GPS by $150.
